reviewText: Boring. I would rent this at Red box for a dollar, but would not recommend buying it.
Great for my collection. Love the way the programs are presented.
NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC IS A GREAT PROGRAM. ANYTHING THAT THE DO, THEY DO IT BEST. WAS VERY HAPPY TO RECEIVE IT.

I bought this to show to my high school students. They were interested in the subject matter and liked the scientific approach to subjects that are considered "spooky" or "scary." I'm glad I got it and recommend it to anyone who would like to explore a more grounded view of the paranormal.
Very Pleased with dealer and the product

This was all about negating and illustrating that there is no proof of anything super natural. Talk about negativity.
This was just ok. I was a little  disappointed with the quality  of the documentaries , especially  coming  from The National  Geographic  Channel .
Horrible. Boring. Filmed bad quality.  Wish I'd never bought it.

THREE discs of Hallowe'en fun!
The National Geographic [Channel] explores supernatural mysteries telling the truth about
[1] ghosts;
[2] hauntings;
[3] vampires;
[4] witchcraft; and,
[5] evil spirits.

The Segments include:

"Is It Real? Ghosts" ; "Is It Real? Hauntings" ; "Is It Real? Vampires" ; "Taboo: Witchcraft" ; "Taboo: Evil Spirits"
Product Details:
  Format: Multiple Formats, Box set, Color, NTSC, Widescreen
  Language: English

FOOTNOTE:
IF you buy the other Nat'l Geo' Classics' title "WITCHES, GHOSTS & MONSTERS"
You'll notice that four of these titles are---ALSO---on that collection:
1.) "Is It Real?: Ghosts"
2.) "Is It Real?: Vampires"
3.) "Is It Real?: Hauntings"
4.) "Taboo: Witchcraft"
BETWEEN THE TWO RELEASES, 8 of 11 titles are different [four are repeated{see above}].
So, if you have both sets, the DIFFERENT EPISODES are:
1.) "Is It Real?: Big Foot"-------- once.
2.) "Is It Real?: Big Foot"-------- once.
3.) "Taboo: Evil Spirits"---------- once.
4.) "Taboo: Devils and Demons"- once.
Great product for the value. Very happy with purchase.
